1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:11,967
<i> Can we start again?</i>

2
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:12,967
<i> Please.</i>

3
00:00:13,100 --> 00:00:14,900
<i> Okay, Sir Tonyo, fresh start.</i>

4
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:17,567
<i>What's important, grandchild,
is you're safe.</i>

5
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:19,333
<i> I owe my life to Tonyo.</i>

6
00:00:19,467 --> 00:00:20,600
<i> Tonyo?</i>

7
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:22,633
<i> No more "Sir"?</i>

8
00:00:22,767 --> 00:00:23,833
<i> I'm just happy.</i>

9
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:27,300
<i>I feel like, from now on,
everything will be fine.</i>

10
00:00:27,433 --> 00:00:29,333
<i>Can't you hear what I'm saying?</i>

11
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:30,833
<i> I want them both gone.</i>

12
00:00:30,967 --> 00:00:32,367
<i> Do you understand that?</i>

13
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:36,733
<i>Get out of there.
I'll blow your head off!</i>

14
00:00:36,867 --> 00:00:37,800
<i> Sir, don't!</i>

15
00:00:37,933 --> 00:00:38,933
<i>- Manang?
- Glen!</i>

16
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:40,967
<i>Do you have to aim at her head?</i>

17
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:43,533
<i>Follow Glen.
I just want to know</i>

18
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:45,800
<i> if my son is human or a demon.</i>

19
00:00:45,933 --> 00:00:47,667
<i>He's already old
but still acts like a baby.</i>

20
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:50,333
<i>Don't get so excited
about those texts.</i>

21
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:52,500
<i>Answer first. Yes or no?
Final answer.</i>

22
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:53,700
<i> Do you love Tonyo?</i>

23
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:56,033
<i> No. We're not yet a couple.</i>

24
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:58,100
<i>So what's that?
No label?</i>

25
00:00:58,233 --> 00:01:00,300
<i> He's not courting you?</i>

26
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:05,767
<i>Bobby, if it's so quick to get,
it's so quick to lose.</i>

27
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:08,933
<i>We should go through
the right process</i>

28
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:10,733
<i> so you don't get hurt.</i>

29
00:01:17,433 --> 00:01:18,700
I'm okay here, Boss.

30
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:19,800
Thank you.

31
00:01:42,933 --> 00:01:44,933
Bossing!

32
00:01:45,067 --> 00:01:47,000
So, how's life?

33
00:01:47,133 --> 00:01:48,600
What are you doing here?

34
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:53,400
Boss, it seems like
you don't want to see us.

35
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:56,900
Sir Tonyo, it seems like you're
waiting for someone there.

36
00:01:58,133 --> 00:02:03,600
No, it's Bobby because she said
she's coming to visit today.

37
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:05,833
Well, Sir, we came
from the police station earlier.

38
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:07,167
She was there.

39
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:09,267
She didn't say anything
about coming here.

40
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,200
Really?

41
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:12,900
She seems busy, Sir.

42
00:02:24,133 --> 00:02:25,733
<i> Hello, Lieutenant Conde?</i>

43
00:02:27,867 --> 00:02:29,800
You're being too formal.

44
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:34,133
You weren't like that
in your texts last night.

45
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:36,933
Sir, I'm sorry, I'm busy.

46
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:39,033
<i> There's work today.</i>

47
00:02:39,167 --> 00:02:40,500
<i>We're the ones assigned
to patrol</i>

48
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:43,567
<i>the remaining fugitive,
Mateo Ramos.</i>

49
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:51,033
Well, I thought you were going
to visit me today.

50
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:56,433
Are you going to replace me
with one of those fugitives?

51
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:03,833
<i>If it's so quick to get,
it's so quick to lose.</i>

52
00:03:03,967 --> 00:03:06,467
<i> We like Sir Tonyo for you,</i>

53
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:10,967
<i>but we should go through
the proper process.</i>

54
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:14,600
<i>To be sure,
so that you don't get hurt.</i>

55
00:03:17,867 --> 00:03:19,100
Ma'am,

56
00:03:19,367 --> 00:03:21,500
a concerned citizen called.

57
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:23,533
Mateo Ramos was spotted.

58
00:03:23,667 --> 00:03:25,767
Sir, I have to go.

59
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:28,867
Wait a minute, Bobby.

60
00:03:30,267 --> 00:03:31,500
We're okay, right?

61
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:34,600
Bobby, Bobby, hello?

62
00:03:38,433 --> 00:03:40,000
Okay, okay...

63
00:03:40,267 --> 00:03:42,033
See you later?

64
00:03:42,467 --> 00:03:44,467
Okay, okay, bye.

65
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:45,633
Let's go.

66
00:03:48,633 --> 00:03:50,833
You're pretending, Sir,
but she hung up on you.

67
00:03:50,967 --> 00:03:51,933
What?

68
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,967
Oh my, Boss,
you're not important.

69
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,833
Why, Sir?
What did you do?

70
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:01,200
Nothing, I don't know.

71
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,167
Oh my, Sir,

72
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:06,533
it's normal for women
to get angry for no reason.

73
00:04:06,667 --> 00:04:07,767
That's right!

74
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:10,933
But even if we don't know
what we did,

75
00:04:11,467 --> 00:04:13,033
we should woo them.

76
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:18,500
You two don't have
any assignments yet, right?

77
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:20,767
Vince,

78
00:04:21,633 --> 00:04:23,600
contact Lee and Bal.

79
00:04:23,733 --> 00:04:24,833
Why, Boss?

80
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:28,533
I'll ask you to do something.

81
00:05:01,567 --> 00:05:02,567
Faye...

82
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:05,733
Maybe you can help us.

83
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:08,800
This is for your sister, Bobby.

84
00:05:09,967 --> 00:05:10,700
Really?

85
00:05:11,767 --> 00:05:13,833
Okay, okay, see you
at the precinct later.

86
00:05:14,067 --> 00:05:15,967
My friend, Allan,
is already there.

87
00:05:16,633 --> 00:05:18,167
Okay, okay.
Be careful!

88
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,667
Nurse, do you know of a place
to buy flowers nearby?

89
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,967
Ah, yes, right there next
to the hospital, there is.

90
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,733
- Why?
- Sir Tonyo asked me

91
00:05:30,867 --> 00:05:31,800
to buy flowers.

92
00:05:31,933 --> 00:05:33,733
He said he's going
to surprise a girl.

93
00:05:34,267 --> 00:05:35,533
Okay, thanks.
I'll go buy some flowers.

94
00:05:35,667 --> 00:05:37,100
Vince! Vince!

95
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:40,233
- Hey.
- I heard what you said earlier.

96
00:05:40,367 --> 00:05:43,667
Sir Tonyo is asking you
to buy flowers.

97
00:05:44,033 --> 00:05:45,233
For whom?

98
00:05:46,467 --> 00:05:47,467
Secret.

99
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,100
You're still being very
secretive about that.

100
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:52,100
I know who they're for.

101
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:54,333
For me.

102
00:05:55,467 --> 00:05:58,333
Last night, I was watching over
Sir Tonyo.

103
00:05:58,467 --> 00:06:00,733
I thought he was sleeping.

104
00:06:00,867 --> 00:06:03,800
I was startled, I saw him
taking a picture of me.

105
00:06:03,933 --> 00:06:06,033
I guess he thought
I was still sleeping.

106
00:06:06,167 --> 00:06:07,633
But when I woke up,

107
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:10,967
he was smiling in the picture
at kissing it.

108
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,133
I'm thrilled.

109
00:06:14,267 --> 00:06:17,667
Oh well, I won't say
you told me.

110
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,633
Just make sure the flowers
are beautiful, okay?

111
00:06:19,767 --> 00:06:21,400
- Okay.
- Thank you.

112
00:06:21,533 --> 00:06:22,633
Yellow!

113
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:23,767
Yellow?

114
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:26,733
We're busted...

115
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:31,300
Oh, sorry.

116
00:06:32,467 --> 00:06:33,867
Hey, those are hospital
supplies!

117
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,100
Why are you taking them home?

118
00:06:35,233 --> 00:06:36,433
Hey, you're crazy...

119
00:06:36,567 --> 00:06:37,567
Hey!

120
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:40,700
You're crazy.

121
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:43,400
Nurse, call the guard!

122
00:06:44,967 --> 00:06:46,167
Manong, are you okay?

123
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:54,000
Madam, everyone,

124
00:06:54,133 --> 00:06:56,767
everything is okay
with the reservation.

125
00:06:56,900 --> 00:07:00,967
Is it okay for you to have
hula-hula dancers?

126
00:07:01,100 --> 00:07:04,700
Then we'll also add tropical
trees on the stage.

127
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,100
There'll be pineapple
decorations.

128
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:07,567
- That'll look good!
- Isn't it lovely, Madam?

129
00:07:07,700 --> 00:07:09,500
- Yes, that's great, Madam.
- I love the pineapple decor.

130
00:07:09,633 --> 00:07:11,700
- Right?
- My friends will be so happy!

131
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:15,533
- That's beautiful!
- That, Madam, oh.

132
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:17,600
That's not what I wanted
to hear.

133
00:07:18,733 --> 00:07:19,933
Joaquin,

134
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:24,333
we've already talked about your
Luau-themed birthday party.

135
00:07:24,467 --> 00:07:26,367
Don't tell me you're going
to change your mind.

136
00:07:26,967 --> 00:07:29,800
I'm fine with those themes.

137
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:34,733
What I just want to hear is,
Bobby invited, okay?

138
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:38,667
But, Joaquin,
this is a public event.

139
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:42,067
Can't you and Bobby just meet,
just the two of you.

140
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,533
And then maybe have
a private dinner?

141
00:07:44,667 --> 00:07:47,400
I'd like all my children
to be there.

142
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:48,767
Mommy,

143
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:49,900
it's daddy's birthday.

144
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:52,033
Grant his request, please.

145
00:07:53,233 --> 00:07:54,800
Okay, fine.

146
00:07:54,933 --> 00:07:56,033
What else?

147
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,467
Excuse me, I have to take this.

148
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,333
Hello? Yeah.

149
00:08:05,467 --> 00:08:06,233
Glen.

150
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,933
Should you stand up?

151
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,933
Who are you talking to?

152
00:08:14,633 --> 00:08:17,733
Cecilia, my girlfriend.

153
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:20,400
Are you sure that's Cecilia?

154
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,533
Can I talk to her?

155
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:25,867
Why?

156
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:27,933
I'm just making sure.

157
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:32,033
If that's really Cecilia,
then I can talk to her.

158
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:37,367
Babe, wait a minute, okay?

159
00:08:39,367 --> 00:08:40,067
Can I?

160
00:08:40,767 --> 00:08:43,567
Dad, why would I lie
about who I'm talking to?

161
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,900
There's nothing wrong
with that, right?

162
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,200
Can I?

163
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:57,967
Yeah, fine.

164
00:09:03,567 --> 00:09:04,533
Hello?

165
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,367
Oh, Cecilia!

166
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,867
See?

167
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:13,967
By the way,

168
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:18,400
I'm inviting you to my birthday
if you have time.

169
00:09:19,133 --> 00:09:20,300
Just drop by.

170
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:21,967
Yes!

171
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,667
Thank you.

172
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:25,867
Okay. Thank you!

173
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:29,600
Is it okay?

174
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,867
- Yeah.
- Babe, I'll call you later.

175
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:39,500
- Dad, are you okay?
- Yes.

176
00:09:39,633 --> 00:09:40,333
You're acting weird.

177
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:41,733
No, no, I'm good.

178
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:43,600
I'm okay.

179
00:10:19,967 --> 00:10:21,767
Sir Tonyo, eat first.

180
00:10:23,067 --> 00:10:25,233
Looks like you woke up
on the right side of the bed.

181
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:27,800
You know why.

182
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,100
Wait...

183
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:33,700
Why is that?

184
00:10:35,867 --> 00:10:36,800
You know, Sir Tonyo,

185
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:38,267
you've been making a lot
of assumptions.

186
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:41,800
Just admit it. You know,
life is too short.

187
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:43,700
Let's get straight
to the point now.

188
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:45,433
Poor Vince.

189
00:10:45,567 --> 00:10:47,500
You even asked him
to do some things.

190
00:10:47,633 --> 00:10:48,767
You know me.

191
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:51,233
My happiness is only
superficial.

192
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:54,067
It's just a small thing,
I'm happy.

193
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,567
Selena, wait...

194
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:59,267
What do you mean?

195
00:10:59,633 --> 00:11:01,100
I know it already.

196
00:11:01,533 --> 00:11:03,400
You're going to surprise me,
aren't you?

197
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:05,833
I saw what you did
last night,

198
00:11:05,967 --> 00:11:07,933
when you took a picture of me
there while I was sleeping.

199
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:09,200
When I opened my eyes,

200
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:13,233
you were smiling and you were
even kissing my picture!

201
00:11:13,367 --> 00:11:15,667
Oh no, Selena...

202
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:20,067
Oh my. No, what, what, what,
what, that...

203
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:22,433
Don't explain.

204
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:25,500
The feeling is mutual.

205
00:11:25,833 --> 00:11:29,400
Later, when you go to sleep,
I'll take a picture of you too.

206
00:11:29,533 --> 00:11:31,133
Selena, sorry.

207
00:11:31,267 --> 00:11:32,533
Just so you know,

208
00:11:34,467 --> 00:11:36,900
I took a picture of you
last night because...

209
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:40,067
I sent it to Bobby.

210
00:11:41,267 --> 00:11:45,433
And then I kissed my phone...

211
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:50,100
because I was texting Bobby.

212
00:11:53,167 --> 00:11:54,167
So...

213
00:11:55,033 --> 00:11:55,767
Wait...

214
00:11:59,667 --> 00:12:01,067
I'm not the one you want?

215
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:09,200
You want Ma'am Bobby?

216
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:16,767
Sir Tonyo, sorry!

217
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:17,933
I'm really sorry!

218
00:12:18,067 --> 00:12:19,700
Lord, I wish the earth
would swallow me right now!

219
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:23,300
I'm so sorry! I didn't mean to!
I thought...

220
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:26,367
- I'm so assuming.
- Stand up. What's with you?

221
00:12:28,167 --> 00:12:30,800
Sir Tonyo, sorry.

222
00:12:30,933 --> 00:12:31,967
Listen.

223
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:36,333
You'll find someone
better than me.

224
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:39,533
You're beautiful and caring.

225
00:12:40,133 --> 00:12:42,467
The guy you'll like
is going to be lucky.

226
00:12:44,933 --> 00:12:47,600
I know that, but...

227
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:50,800
Wait...

228
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:55,033
Does Ma'am Bobby know
that you like her?

229
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:58,367
Does Ma'am Bobby like you, too?

230
00:13:01,167 --> 00:13:02,700
Is that important?

231
00:13:03,267 --> 00:13:04,467
Why isn't it important?

232
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:05,933
No.

233
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:33,400
Mayor, I'm going
to follow Glen now.

234
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:47,800
Yes, Sir, Ma'am,
I'm Jesus Sevilla,

235
00:13:47,933 --> 00:13:50,233
but I didn't call the police.

236
00:13:50,833 --> 00:13:52,633
But this is your number, right?

237
00:13:52,767 --> 00:13:57,367
0-9-4-6-5-5-6-7-8-2-2.

238
00:13:57,533 --> 00:13:58,467
Yes, Sir.

239
00:13:58,900 --> 00:13:59,967
What is this about?

240
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:02,467
Am I breaking the law?

241
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:05,067
I'm not doing anything wrong.

242
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:08,467
According to the caller,
Jesus Sevilla.

243
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:12,000
He said he saw the fugitive
in the area, Mateo Ramos.

244
00:14:12,133 --> 00:14:13,500
I'm sorry, Ma'am, Sir,

245
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:16,033
but that's impossible.

246
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:17,400
I'm blind.

247
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:23,700
Raffy, Emong!

248
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:26,433
You did this again!

249
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,300
Excuse me, Ma'am, Sir.

250
00:14:29,667 --> 00:14:32,000
Those two jerks played a prank
on me again.

251
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:34,167
They often do that to me.

252
00:14:34,733 --> 00:14:36,367
Raffy, Emong...

253
00:14:36,733 --> 00:14:38,333
Can we talk to you?

254
00:14:38,667 --> 00:14:40,300
- They'll talk to us.
- Let's go.

255
00:14:41,467 --> 00:14:42,633
Hey, wait a minute!

256
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:49,567
Dante, where are you?

257
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:52,667
I'm just going around
Apitong Street.

258
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:56,233
Someone's been following me
for a while.

259
00:14:56,933 --> 00:14:59,400
I can already see your car,
Boss, and the motorbike.

260
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:00,733
We're tailing you already.

261
00:15:00,867 --> 00:15:01,933
Good.

262
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:07,133
See that blue motorbike
with the black helmet?

263
00:15:07,267 --> 00:15:09,067
It's been following me
for a while.

264
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,367
Copy, Boss.
We'll take care of it.

265
00:15:21,733 --> 00:15:23,600
Because even if she doesn't
want me,

266
00:15:24,533 --> 00:15:26,567
I'll still do this.

267
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:31,067
Now, if she wants me,
then that's a bonus.

268
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:36,200
Ma'am Bobby is lucky
to have you.

269
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:39,500
No, Selena.

270
00:15:41,300 --> 00:15:42,600
I'm luckier.

271
00:16:02,967 --> 00:16:04,767
Quick! There they are!

272
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:05,800
Hey!

273
00:16:12,533 --> 00:16:13,567
Hey!

274
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,467
- Get down!
- Get down!

275
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:18,433
Come with us to the precinct!

276
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:20,333
You can be punished
for what you did!

277
00:16:20,467 --> 00:16:24,033
You've inconvenienced our time,
and you even caused an accident!

278
00:16:24,167 --> 00:16:25,867
You're something else!
Noble, handcuff him!

279
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,467
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Let us go!

280
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,733
The village captain here
is our godfather!

281
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:29,633
Yes, that's true!

282
00:16:29,767 --> 00:16:31,367
Hey, there's no godfather here.

283
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:32,833
You can even take him with you.

284
00:16:32,967 --> 00:16:33,933
Don't resist.

285
00:16:34,067 --> 00:16:35,367
I'll kill you.

286
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:41,000
Sir, how is he doing?

287
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:42,967
Ma'am, we'll take you
to the hospital.

288
00:16:43,133 --> 00:16:43,967
What a pity.

289
00:16:44,367 --> 00:16:45,733
Oh, okay, thank you.

290
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:49,033
<i>Poor mister. Let's take him
to the hospital, okay?</i>

291
00:16:57,933 --> 00:17:00,300
Let's go! Okay! Stand up!

292
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:03,433
- Let's take him to the car.
- Yes, Ma'am. Let's go!

293
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:07,867
You're annoying, okay.

294
00:17:11,567 --> 00:17:12,333
Get in.

295
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:17,800
You two, what you did
was wrong, okay.

296
00:17:17,967 --> 00:17:20,733
The blind man is working hard
and living quietly.

297
00:17:20,867 --> 00:17:22,167
And then you're going
to do this?

298
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:24,067
You're going to use him
for a prank call?

299
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,733
What for?

300
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:28,433
To make him think
that you two are superior

301
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:29,733
because he's disabled.

302
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:32,833
- Sorry, Mother.
- Sorry, Mother.

303
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,433
Your parents
didn't raise you properly.

304
00:17:35,567 --> 00:17:38,700
Well, this prison cell
will fix you.

305
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:41,733
Hey, that prank calling,
that's five years here,

306
00:17:41,867 --> 00:17:43,533
or you'll pay forty thousand.

307
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:48,267
Espina,

308
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:49,700
it looks like you're going
to be transferred

309
00:17:49,833 --> 00:17:51,200
to Calabari State Prison.

310
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,433
Your lawyer is already there,
talking to Chief.

311
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,600
They're already arranging
your hearing schedule.

312
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:02,467
Hey, you two, behave,
while it's still early.

313
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:05,933
- Sorry, Mother.
- Sorry, Mother

314
00:18:06,067 --> 00:18:07,033
You're annoying.

315
00:18:08,867 --> 00:18:11,833
Noble, what's the news
about the delivery rider

316
00:18:11,967 --> 00:18:13,000
who fell earlier?

317
00:18:13,133 --> 00:18:14,100
Nothing, Ma'am.

318
00:18:14,233 --> 00:18:16,767
I didn't get the details
of the two who helped him.

319
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:17,933
But they were kind enough,

320
00:18:18,067 --> 00:18:19,733
to take the rider
to the hospital.

321
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,767
Who ordered you to follow
the Vice Mayor?

322
00:18:27,467 --> 00:18:29,867
Admit it before he even
gets here!

323
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:34,600
I don't know anything
about what you're saying.

324
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:42,233
What's the news here?

325
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:45,767
Boss, he still refuses
to admit anything.

326
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:47,367
Where did you get this?

327
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:53,133
From the boss's sister,
the policeman.

328
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:54,800
Bobby?

329
00:18:55,233 --> 00:18:57,400
Bobby and her partner
are chasing some jerks.

330
00:18:58,033 --> 00:19:00,700
He passed by,
had an accident,

331
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:03,200
that's why we brought him here.

332
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:06,667
Imagine that,
she's able to help us.

333
00:19:08,033 --> 00:19:11,167
My illegitimate sister
has a use somehow.

334
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:20,800
- I'll take care of this.
- I'll go ahead.

335
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,233
Just wait there.

336
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:30,733
- Oh, relax, relax!
- Easy! Easy. High blood.

337
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:32,867
- Ma'am Bobby! It's just us!
- Bobby!

338
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,133
These guys are crazy.

339
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:35,567
Faye,

340
00:19:36,267 --> 00:19:37,600
what are you doing here?

341
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:39,700
Tonyo wants to talk to you.

342
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:42,133
- Bossing! Boss!
- Boss Tonyo, oh!

343
00:19:42,267 --> 00:19:43,500
Hi, Bobby!

344
00:19:43,633 --> 00:19:46,000
Faye has nothing to do
with this.

345
00:19:46,133 --> 00:19:46,867
It's just me.

346
00:19:47,633 --> 00:19:48,733
Bobby,

347
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:52,600
I don't know why you suddenly
seem to feel bad about me.

348
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:58,333
But I have something written
that I want to hear.

349
00:19:58,733 --> 00:20:01,233
I couldn't sleep
while writing this,

350
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,533
so I hope you can listen to it.

351
00:20:03,667 --> 00:20:05,900
Lee, Bal, what, are you ready?

352
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:08,100
Boss, of course!
Ready, ready, ready!

353
00:20:08,233 --> 00:20:11,167
- Dude, get that beat going.
- Okay.

354
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:12,333
Okay.

355
00:20:15,433 --> 00:20:19,467
Good morning, beautiful lady.
We have a boss,

356
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:20,967
you're the one he chooses.

357
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:23,733
You're the reason for the smile
on his lips.

358
00:20:23,867 --> 00:20:25,800
He loves someone,
and her name is...

359
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:26,933
Bobby!

360
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:30,367
See, I wrote something long,
right?

361
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,233
What a thrill!

362
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,467
Faye, can you come closer?

363
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,433
Oh, come closer.
That, that, that!

364
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:46,133
By the way, Bobby,

365
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:52,500
can we go on a date later
here at the hospital?

366
00:20:55,667 --> 00:20:57,933
Yes, where's the gift?

367
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,533
There it is, Ma'am.

368
00:21:01,767 --> 00:21:02,600
What is this?

369
00:21:02,733 --> 00:21:04,133
Open it, Bobby.

370
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,800
It's beautiful!

371
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,600
- That's sexy!
- That's beautiful!

372
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:11,200
- Hey!
- Wow.

373
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:12,767
That's for you.

374
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:14,767
I hope you'll come later.

375
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,033
What's with you, Sir?

376
00:21:16,167 --> 00:21:17,800
I haven't agreed yet.

377
00:21:17,933 --> 00:21:18,867
Please.

378
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:23,000
- That's okay!
- Okay, that's okay!

379
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:26,633
Okay, okay.

380
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,067
Really?

381
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:30,700
Yes!

382
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:31,833
You're welcome, Boss!

383
00:21:31,967 --> 00:21:33,033
Bal, give me a beat!

384
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:37,400
Ma'am Bobby has accepted
the flowers!

385
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:39,967
So let's all clap now.

386
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:41,533
Hands up!

387
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:43,000
- Hands up!
- Yeah!

388
00:21:43,133 --> 00:21:48,600
Madam has accepted the flowers!
So let's all clap now.

389
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:49,733
Hands up!

390
00:21:49,867 --> 00:21:51,167
Hands up!

391
00:21:51,300 --> 00:21:52,467
- Hands up!
- Yeah!

392
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:53,500
Hands up!

393
00:21:58,800 --> 00:22:00,867
That's enough, that's enough,
that's enough.

394
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:02,333
That's enough.

395
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,467
It's over, Boss.

396
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:11,467
His eyes are closed.

397
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:13,100
He is used to being beaten.

398
00:22:13,233 --> 00:22:14,900
He won't talk anymore.

399
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:17,200
Where's his cell phone?

400
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:18,233
This, boss.

401
00:22:20,500 --> 00:22:23,900
Let's see who the last person
this animal talked to.

402
00:22:31,667 --> 00:22:32,700
Jun!

403
00:22:32,833 --> 00:22:35,033
I've been waiting for your call.

404
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,633
Do you have an update?

405
00:22:36,767 --> 00:22:38,767
Have you discovered anything
about Glen?

406
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:41,200
Hello, Jun? Jun!

407
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:45,467
Hello, Jun!

408
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,867
You're an animal.

409
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,700
My father is your boss.

410
00:23:27,067 --> 00:23:28,733
Lieutenant Conde is so sweet.

411
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:31,100
Even though he was injured
and hospitalized,

412
00:23:31,233 --> 00:23:34,767
he still found a way to court
Sergeant Enriquez.

413
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:37,233
It's like there are no such men
anymore.

414
00:23:37,367 --> 00:23:38,733
Selena, are you mad?

415
00:23:38,867 --> 00:23:40,100
Are you going to fight me?

416
00:23:40,233 --> 00:23:44,100
If so, you've seen
how I fight, right?

417
00:23:44,233 --> 00:23:45,133
Do you think, Boss,

418
00:23:45,267 --> 00:23:47,433
that he said anything about us
to your sister

419
00:23:47,567 --> 00:23:48,633
who is a police offcer?

420
00:23:48,767 --> 00:23:51,433
Well, I'm sorry, his bastard
daughter will be involved.

421
00:23:51,567 --> 00:23:52,200
Jun!

422
00:23:52,333 --> 00:23:54,233
Why can't I contact you?

423
00:23:54,367 --> 00:23:57,667
Dad, you look like
you've seen a ghost.

424
00:23:57,833 --> 00:23:59,767
Thank you so much for coming.

425
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:00,900
Why, Bobby?

426
00:24:01,033 --> 00:24:01,733
Are you mad?
